# Project Methodology

The project followed a structured analytics workflow.

## Step 1: Data Collection

Four healthcare datasets were collected and imported into Python.

## Step 2: Data Cleaning

Data quality checks were performed to ensure consistency across all datasets. Missing values, duplicate records, and inconsistent data types were handled before analysis.

## Step 3: Data Integration

The Patients, Doctors, Admissions, and Outcomes datasets were merged into a single analytical dataset using common identifiers.

## Step 4: Feature Engineering

Additional business metrics were created to improve analysis, including:

* Length of Stay
* Cost per Day
* Age Group
* Admission Month
* Admission Year

These engineered features enabled more meaningful business analysis and visualization.

## Step 5: Exploratory Data Analysis

Python was used to identify patterns in:

* Disease distribution
* Department performance
* Treatment costs
* Patient demographics
* Hospital stay duration
* Recovery outcomes

## Step 6: SQL Business Analysis

Advanced SQL queries were developed to answer business questions related to:

* Department performance
* Readmission rates
* Doctor rankings
* Patient satisfaction
* Treatment costs
* Hospital admissions

The analysis utilized joins, common table expressions (CTEs), window functions, ranking functions, and subqueries.

## Step 7: Dashboard Development

Power BI dashboards were developed to provide an interactive view of hospital operations and patient care metrics.

